---
import Link from '@/components/Link.astro'
import PageHead from '@/components/PageHead.astro'
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout class="max-w-3xl">
  <PageHead slot="head" title="Colophon" />
  
  <article class="prose prose-gray dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h1>Colophon</h1>
    
    <p>
      This site is built with a focus on simplicity, performance, and longevity. 
      The design philosophy prioritizes content over chrome, readability over novelty.
    </p>

    <h2>Technology</h2>
    
    <p>The site is built using:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://astro.build" external>Astro</Link> — A modern static site generator 
        that ships zero JavaScript by default
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://tailwindcss.com" external>Tailwind CSS</Link> — For utility-first styling
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://ui.shadcn.com" external>shadcn/ui</Link> — For accessible UI components
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://www.typescriptlang.org" external>TypeScript</Link> — For type safety
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Typography</h2>
    
    <p>
      The site uses system fonts for optimal performance and native feel. 
      Text is set in your operating system's default sans-serif font stack, 
      ensuring fast load times and familiar reading experience.
    </p>

    <h2>Design Principles</h2>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Performance first</strong> — Every decision considers load time and runtime performance</li>
      <li><strong>Progressive enhancement</strong> — The site works without JavaScript</li>
      <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> — WCAG compliant with semantic HTML and proper ARIA labels</li>
      <li><strong>Longevity</strong> — Built to last with minimal dependencies and standard web technologies</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Inspiration</h2>
    
    <p>
      This site draws inspiration from several sources that exemplify thoughtful web design:
    </p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://gwern.net" external>Gwern Branwen</Link> — For demonstrating the power 
        of information density and long-form content
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://frankchimero.com" external>Frank Chimero</Link> — For elegant simplicity
      </li>
      <li>
        <Link href="https://craigmod.com" external>Craig Mod</Link> — For thoughtful typography 
        and reading experience
      </li>
      <li>
        The newspaper layouts from my time at The Washington Post — For modular, flexible content systems
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    
    <p>
      This site collects no analytics, sets no tracking cookies, and stores no personal data. 
      What you read is your business.
    </p>

    <h2>Source</h2>
    
    <p>
      The source code for this site is available on 
      <Link href="https://github.com/rmbrntt/ryanbarnett.dev" external>GitHub</Link>.
      Feel free to explore, learn, or adapt anything you find useful.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    
    <p>
      You can reach me via email at <Link href="mailto:hello@ryanbarnett.dev">hello@ryanbarnett.dev</Link> 
      or find me on <Link href="https://github.com/rmbrntt" external>GitHub</Link>.
    </p>

    <hr />
    
    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
        year: 'numeric',
        month: 'long',
        day: 'numeric'
      })}
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>